{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"7457","heading":"On-call pay","label":"7457 On-call pay","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptV/ch74/schIV","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Prior ProvisionsProvisions similar to those in this section were contained in prior to the repeal of that section as part of the complete revision of chapter 73 of this title by .section 4107(j) of this titlePub. L. 102–40"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may pay an employee to whom this section applies pay at the rate provided in except for such time as the employee may be called back to work.section 7453(h) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The employee is employed in a position listed in paragraph (3) of or meets the criteria specified in clauses (i), (ii), and (iii) of .section 7401 of this titlesection 7455(a)(2)(B) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The employee is employed in a work unit for which on-call premium pay is authorized.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The employee is officially scheduled to be on call outside such employee’s regular hours or on a holiday designated by Federal statute or Executive order.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the rate of pay which such employee would receive if being paid the rate of standby pay pursuant to such section that such individual would be entitled to receive if such individual were not scheduled to be on call instead, or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s7457/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs7457%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the rate of pay which such employee is entitled to receive including on-call premium pay described in subsection (a).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
